FBIS4-27730 "dreas108_j_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-108 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 Indonesia Minister Stresses No Foreign Investment Minister Stresses No Foreign Investment BK0606075694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in Indonesian 0700 GMT 6 Jun 94 BK0606075694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network Indonesian BFN [Text] Information Minister Harmoko has stated that President Suharto will not issue a presidential decree on foreign investment in mass media although such investment is permitted under Government Regulation No. 20/1994. Speaking to reporters after meeting the president at Merdeka Palace this afternoon, the information minister urged the general public to stop making a fuss over the matter because the president's policy is clear. Harmoko subsequently urged the general public to stop questioning Government Regulation No. 20, particularly the clause on possible foreign investment in mass media through joint ventures. He also informed the head of state of the indefinite postponement of the Islamic Conference Organization information ministers conference.
